title: William Morris Leicester Earrings
description:
Leicester, the inspiration for these earrings, is a pattern created in 1911 by John Henry Dearle for Morris & Company. Dearle was a profilic designer and exhibited many early patterns under the Morris name. Ships nicely boxed and ready for gifting.

  • Dimensions: 2 in.
  • Materials: solid brass, electro-plated with gold finish, giclee print, domed, ear wires are gold plated
